===Etymology===
Arabic {{Arab|[[صوم]]}} ''{{IPAchar|(ʂawm)}}'' (fasting, abstaining from food, drink, and sex) < [[Syriac]] ''sawmo''.

===Noun===
'''sawm'''

# {{Islam}} [[fasting]], [[abstention]], [[abstinence]]; the third of the [[five pillars]] of [[Islam]] (during the month of [[Ramadan]], Muslims abstain from food, drink, gambling, and all sensuous pleasures from sunrise to sunset. '''Sawm''' is regulated by Islamic [[jurisprudence]]. Contrary to popular non-Islamic belief, its observance by [[Muslim]]s is not confined to the [[Islamic]] holy month of [[Ramadan]].)

